  <div class="page-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">

        <h2>What we do</h2>
        <p>BuilderSoftwareGuide publishes in-depth reviews and comparisons of construction project management software. Our goal is simple: help general contractors, homebuilders, and remodelers choose tools that actually fit their business — without sitting through a sales demo to get basic pricing information.</p>

        <p>Construction software is a crowded, confusing market. Vendors rarely publish clear pricing. Features overlap. And the "best" tool depends heavily on what type of work you do, how many projects you run at once, and whether you're a crew of 5 or 50.</p>

        <p>We cut through that noise with specific, honest recommendations.</p>

        <h2>Our methodology</h2>
        <p>Every software we review gets evaluated across the same dimensions:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Pricing transparency</strong> — We document actual published pricing tiers, not "contact us for a quote" non-answers (though we note when vendors don't publish pricing).</li>
          <li><strong>Core feature coverage</strong> — Scheduling, budgeting, subcontractor management, client communication, and job costing.</li>
          <li><strong>Use-case fit</strong> — Homebuilder tools aren't right for commercial GCs. We're explicit about who each platform is actually designed for.</li>
          <li><strong>Learning curve and support</strong> — Onboarding complexity is real. We call it out.</li>
          <li><strong>Honest cons</strong> — Every platform has weaknesses. We list them.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we make money</h2>
        <p>This site earns affiliate commissions from some of the software we review. When you click a link to Buildertrend, Houzz Pro, or another tool and sign up, we may receive a commission. This doesn't cost you anything extra.</p>

        <p>We disclose affiliate relationships clearly and don't let them influence our rankings or recommendations. We've recommended software with no affiliate program when it was the right fit for the reader. <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Read our full affiliate disclosure →</a></p>

        <h2>Sister site</h2>
        <p>BuilderSoftwareGuide is part of a small portfolio of independent software review sites. Our sister site, <a href="https://www.tradesoftwareguide.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TradeSoftwareGuide.com</a>, covers field service software for HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and cleaning businesses. If you're a trade contractor (not primarily a builder or GC), that site will be more relevant to your needs.</p>

        <h2>Contact us</h2>
        <p>Questions, corrections, or suggestions? Email us at <a href="mailto:team@buildersoftwareguide.com">team@buildersoftwareguide.com</a>. We read everything.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
